The paper proposes a novel solution for Multilinear Compressive Learning (MCL) that combines compressive sensing and machine learning. The paper focuses on finding a discriminative tensor subspace and optimizing the system to project the signals onto that data manifold. This work is related to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT). However, given the focus on machine learning and the use of supervised and semi-supervised learning techniques, cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.CV due to the use of compressive sensing in image and video processing.
